I think this might be related to my having two screens (Display :0.0 and :0.1)
If I start xfce4-terminal on the second screen (:0.1), and then launch it again on the other screen (0.0), it seems to crash.

Can you attach output of 'xrandr -q' ?
Are these seperate hardware displays? Or ?

I have two monitors, each attached to a different graphics card: an AOC monitor attached via DVI to 01:00.0 (see lspci output below) and an Iiyama monitor attached to 02:00.0.
